*portage_mod_jabber-0.0.7 (21 Aug 2013)
	21 Aug 2013; Raphaël Barrois <gentoo@xelnor.net>
	Refactored the whole project to use sleekxmpp, and add Python3
	compatibility.

*portage_mod_jabber-0.0.6 (11 Apr 2013)
	11 Apr 2013; Raphaël Barrois <gentoo@xelnor.net>
	Refactored the whole project to use pyxmpp, and add Python3
	compatibility.

	23 Jul 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Refactored the internal structure to reuse the XMPP client object for each
	message sent

	23 Jul 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	License changed to GPL 3

	23 Jul 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Bring back the possibility to replace %hostname% in the sender resource
	with the hostname of the machine the machine plugin is running. This
	regression was introduced in 0.0.5

*portage_mod_jabber-0.0.5.1 (6 Jul 2008)
	6 Jul 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Bugfix release to be compatible with portage 2.2 and 2.0.x

*portage_mod_jabber-0.0.5 (5 Jul 2008)
	5 Jul 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Allow specifying the sender JID in a more standardized way:
	node:pw@host.com[/resource]

*portage-mod_jabber-0.0.3 (3 Jan 2008)
	3 Jan 2008; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Added a facility to specify the Jabber resource. It is also possible to
	use %hostname% in the resource string and get it replaced with the systems
	hostname

*portage-mod_jabber-0.0.2 (30 May 2005)
	21 May 2006; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Fixed a missing "raise" on throwing a PortageException and deactivate the
	debugging mechanism for xmpppy to reflect the introducation per default
	in version 0.3.1 of xmpppy (http://xmpppy.sourceforge.net/)

*portage-mod_jabber-0.0.1 (21 May 2006)
	21 May 2006; Lars Strojny <lars@strojny.net>
	Initial release
